SIMPLE: edible
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Edible
<hw>Ed"i*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>edibilis</ets>, fr. <ets>edere</ets> to eat. See
<er>Eat</er>.]</ety> <def>Fit to be eaten as food; eatable; esculent;
<as>as, <ex>edible</ex> fishes</as>.</def> <au>Bacon.</au> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>Anything edible.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Edible bird's nest</b></col>. <cd>See <er>Bird's
nest</er>, 2.</cd> -- <col><b>Edible crab</b></col>
<fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld>, <cd>any species of crab used as food, esp. the
American blue crab (<spn>Callinectes hastatus</spn>). See
<er>Crab</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Edible frog</b></col>
<fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld>, <cd>the common European frog (<spn>Rana
esculenta</spn>), used as food.</cd> -- <col><b>Edible snail</b></col>
<fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld>, <cd>any snail used as food, esp. <spn>Helix
pomatia</spn> and <spn>H. aspersa</spn> of Europe.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Edibleness</ent>⟦br⟧
